<subSubSection id="BBDF650A4F00FFC9FA80FB0E1453FAD1" pageId="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F37A36814F00FFC9FA80FB0E1453FAD1" blockId="8.[151,1436,1173,1331]" pageId="8">
<emphasis id="C1B1EA934F00FFC9FA80FB0E1625FB2D" bold="true" box="[199,315,1206,1231]" pageId="8">Remarks.</emphasis>
The occurrence of this Sibero-European species on this Mediterranean island is significant because of its low thermophily and because its southern limits in Europe still need to be defined (see e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="97544B704F00FFC9FEBAFB6F1286FB12" author="Poisson, R." box="[1277,1432,1239,1264]" pageId="8" refId="ref9925" refString="Poisson, R. (1957) Heteropteres aquatiques. Faune de France. Vol. 61. Federation Francaise des Societes de Sciences Naturelles, Paris, 263 pp." type="book" year="1957">Poisson 1957</bibRefCitation>
, Cianferoni 2011, Cianferoni 
<emphasis id="C1B1EA934F00FFC9FB90FB421511FAF3" box="[471,527,1273,1297]" italics="true" pageId="8">et al.</emphasis>
2011, 
<bibRefCitation id="97544B704F00FFC9F81DFB41149CFAF0" author="Cianferoni, F. &amp; Mazza, G." box="[602,898,1273,1298]" pageId="8" pagination="36 - 52" refId="ref8388" refString="Cianferoni, F. &amp; Mazza, G. (2012) The aquatic Heteroptera (Insecta: Hemiptera) of the &quot; Foreste Casentinesi, Monte Falterona e Campigna &quot; National Park (Central Italy). Zootaxa, 3568, 36 - 52." type="journal article" year="2012">Cianferoni &amp; Mazza 2012</bibRefCitation>
). The presence also of the more thermophilic 
<taxonomicName id="34C54D024F00FFC9FF3AFB4217E2FAD0" baseAuthorityName="Dufour" baseAuthorityYear="1833" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaea">
<emphasis id="C1B1EA934F00FFC9FF3AFB4217E2FAD0" italics="true" pageId="8">M. pygmaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on Corfu is possible, although it has not been found.
</paragraph>
